FEELING LIKE KINGS! SUPER RUGBY STATUS CONFIRMED. The long awaited announcement of 16 August 2012 that the EP Kings will be playing Super Rugby nex t year in the guise of the Southern Kings will go down as one of the great days in the history of the sport in the Eastern Cape. EP Rugby Union President Cheeky Watson says the news was celebrated from George to Mthatha and beyond. However, he feels the deal in its current form is not good for South African rugby as a whole...
